You’re asking for Java to list fields in a table — but tables aren’t native to Java. You probably mean SQL.

If you want the column names from an actual database table, use JDBC:

```java
String url = "jdbc:yourdb://localhost/dbname";
String user = "user", pass = "pass";

try (Connection conn = DriverManager.getConnection(url, user, pass);
     Statement stmt = conn.createStatement();
     ResultSetMetaData metaData = stmt.executeQuery("SELECT * FROM your_table LIMIT 1").getMetaData()) {

    int columnCount = metaData.getColumnCount();
    for (int i = 1; i <= columnCount; ++i) {
        System.out.println(metaData.getColumnName(i));
    }
} catch (SQLException e) { 
    throw new RuntimeException(e); // or handle as needed
}
```

Replace `yourdb`, `localhost`, and `your_table`. Works for most JDBC drivers.

